to run the AlarmClock program, first you need to connect the database driver. 

1: to connect using eclipse. right click on the default package -> build path -> configure build  	path -> libraries -> add external JARs -> derbyclient.jar -> ok

2: run the server. usually locate at the directory where we install the JDK.
   go to  "/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/db/bin" and run "startNetworkServer"
   you may run with sudo if denied access due to priviledge

